2|Grease and flour your cake baking pan and set aside. 
1|Preheat your oven to 325 degrees F.
3|Mix together all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl: flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
3|Make three holes with a spatula or mixing spoon. 
3|Pour the oil in one of the holes, the vinegar in another hole and the vanilla in the last hole.
3|Add the cold water on top of all of the chocolate cake ingredients.
3|Start your mixer out on low and increase the speed as your ingredients begin to come together. 
3|Continue to mix until all of the ingredients are incorporated and the chocolate cake mixture is smooth.
4|Pour your chocolate cake mixture into your baking pan scraping the sides and bottom with your spatula. 
4|Settle or spread the mixture into the pan evenly.
4|Bake on 325 degrees F for about 1 hour. 
5|Check to see if cake is ready by using a cake tester.
